### **Why Jewelers Don't Tell You**

Most retailers are happy to collect the **$2,130 "Paper Premium"** on that 1-carat E-color stone. However, once the stone is in the ring, a GIA grader cannot technically verify it is "Flawless" because the prongs hide the very areas where surface blemishes (the difference between FL and IF) occur.

You are effectively paying for a "ghost" grade that can no longer be proven once the jewelry is finished.

> 
> 
> You are paying a 40% premium for a "Flawless" certificate. The second the ring is built, the structural friction technically downgrades it. You paid for perfection that literally cannot survive the manufacturing process.  
